# QA_Test_Plan

## 1. Applies when
Always. QA planning is a baseline requirement for any shipped product.

## 2. This document owns
QA strategy, test phases, and coverage targets; functional testing: gameplay, systems, progression, save/load; compatibility testing: platforms, hardware configurations, OS versions; performance testing: frame rate, memory, load times, stress tests; compliance testing: platform certification requirements (Xbox, PlayStation, Steam); bug tracking workflow and severity classification; automation testing strategy and tooling.

## 3. This document does NOT own
Game design validation (→ Design_Document, verified via audit); specific gameplay balance values (→ Gameplay_Systems); build and release pipeline (→ Build_And_Release); localization testing (→ Localization, coordinates with QA).

## 4. Recommended chapter structure
1. QA Strategy & Test Phases · 2. Functional Testing · 3. Compatibility Testing · 4. Performance Testing · 5. Compliance Testing · 6. Bug Tracking & Severity · 7. Automation Testing

## 5. Common boundaries
- QA owns "what to test and how"; Gameplay_Systems owns "what the correct behavior is".
- Performance targets belong here; rendering budgets belong to Technical_Design.
- Compliance checklists belong here; platform-specific implementations belong to Technical_Design.

## 6. Common audit rules
- Check that test coverage references enabled game systems from Gameplay_Systems.
- Check that compliance targets reference platform documentation.
